	<p>
	<font size = 2>
	<p>John is the President of Naleco Research Inc. <a href="http://www.naleco.com">Naleco Research</a> is the developer of RADFind 96, an acclaimed high-speed file finder for Windows 95. Naleco Research also has under development a number of exciting new tools that will enhance the COM and ActiveX experience for all developers.</p>
<p>John frequently contributes to the pages of PC Magazine, with articles relating to COM, OLE and ActiveX technologies. Many of his articles can be found on Naleco Research's new IUnknown.com <a href="http://www.iunknown.com">web site</a>, as well as on PC Magazines <a href="http://www.pcmag.com">web site</a>.</p>
<p>John will be teaching the Essential COM course at <a href="http://www.develop.com">DevelopMentor</a> starting in October. Look to DevelopMentor for all of your COM training needs. They are truly a very cool company to be associated with.</p>
<p>John also speaks annually at the <a href="http://www.borland.com/borcon97">Borland Developer's Conference</a>, and will be appearing again this year in Nashville. Look for his talks on the new Dual Interface features in Delphi 3, and Fusing Win32 Applications with the Windows Shell.</p>
<p>John has shipped numerous shrink-wrapped applications recently, and for the Commodore PET / 64 computers in the distant past. One of the many diversions that he has had in his life culminated in the receipt of a Doctorate in Organic Chemistry from the University of Toronto.</p><br>
